inside e-mail
Emanuel AME Church, including
its pastor,

44:05.610 --> 44:11.182 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Reverend Clementa Pinckney.
Alleged white
supremacist Dylann Roof was
charged on multiple

44:11.215 --> 44:15.419 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
counts, including murder and
hate crimes.
He could face the death penalty.

44:15.453 --> 44:20.157 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This past winter, the Reverend
Betty Deas
Clark took over as Emanuel's
pastor.

44:20.191 --> 44:24.595 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown spoke with her
recently, before
this week's shootings. She
traveled to Orlando

44:24.629 --> 44:29.534 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
yesterday to support families
there and to
speak out in favor of gun
control.

44:29.567 --> 44:33.905 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Rev. Dr. Clark,
thank you for
letting us come visit.

44:33.938 --> 44:35.473 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REV. DR. BETTY DEAS CLARK,
Pastor, Emanuel
AME Church: Thank you for
coming.

44:35.506 --> 44:37.408 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Let me ask you,
one year later,
how is your congregation faring?

44:37.441 --> 44:43.347 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REV. BETTY DEAS CLARK: Well, I
would like
to think that they're
processing, but yet

44:43.381 --> 44:50.488 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
still grieving. It's a process
that may take
years, but it's good to see
signs of them

44:50.521 --> 44:52.857 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
being able to smile, to laugh
again.

44:52.890 --> 44:57.995 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Right away, of
course, there
were expressions of forgiveness
to an extent

44:58.029 --> 45:02.199 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that I think amazed many in the
nation and
around the world.

45:02.233 --> 45:09.407 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Is that still the sense that is
there, the
forgiveness, or are there other
emotions involved

45:09.440 --> 45:11.175 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
as well?

45:11.208 --> 45:16.213 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REV. BETTY DEAS CLARK: Well,
there are an
array of emotions. But
forgiveness is more

45:16.247 --> 45:25.189 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
than an emotion. It is a choice.
And so while
we confess forgiveness, we yet
still have

45:25.222 --> 45:29.327 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
feelings of many different
degrees, and that's
OK.

45:29.360 --> 45:31.095 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Anger?

45:31.128 --> 45:37.535 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REV. BETTY DEAS CLARK: It's OK
to be angry.
It's OK. It's OK to be tearful.
It's OK to

45:37.568 --> 45:43.641 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
sometimes want to pull away from
the world
and just be by yourself. It's
OK, because

45:43.674 --> 45:49.113 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the road and the path for
grieving, it's different
for every individual.

45:49.146 --> 45:55.786 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: As a pastor, I
wonder, do you
think, how could this happen,
where is God,

45:55.820 --> 45:57.655 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
where was God at this moment?

45:57.688 --> 46:02.460 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REV. BETTY DEAS CLARK: Well, my
first response
was just as they were in Bible
study on that

46:02.493 --> 46:12.770 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Wednesday night, so was I. And
so I guess
my first line of questioning
was, why them?

46:12.803 --> 46:16.874 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then it was to say, it could
have been
me.

46:16.907 --> 46:24.315 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But to say where was God, I
never asked that
question, simply because I truly
believe that

46:24.348 --> 46:30.588 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
God is omniscient. In other
words, he's everywhere
at the same time. And I believe,
that if God

46:30.621 --> 46:33.424 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
allowed it, he had a reason for
doing so.

46:33.457 --> 46:39.196 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: This congregation
and you yourself
have spoken out about gun
control issues in

46:39.230 --> 46:39.897 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the aftermath, correct?

46:39.930 --> 46:41.132 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
REV. BETTY DEAS CLARK: Correct.

46:41.165 --> 46:42.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And what would
you like to
see happen?

46:42.967 --> 46:47.872 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REV. BETTY DEAS CLARK: Well, I
would like
to see situations such as the
case with Dylann

46:47.905 --> 46:53.744 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Roof and not having a proper
complete background
check, I would like to see that
come to an

46:53.778 --> 46:55.713 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
end.

46:55.746 --> 47:01.886 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I would like to see that loop
closed, because
it has already shown us how
dangerous it actually

47:01.919 --> 47:08.125 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is, and can be again, until we
do something
positive and permanently about
it.

47:08.159 --> 47:13.330 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Dylann Roof
himself now faces
the death penalty. Do you
yourself have feelings

47:13.364 --> 47:14.832 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
about that?

47:14.865 --> 47:19.103 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
REV. BETTY DEAS CLARK: I never
considered
myself neither judge nor jury.

47:19.136 --> 47:26.544 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But what I see is a young man
who -- someone
once asked me, if I were to meet
him, if he

47:26.577 --> 47:31.916 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
were to ask to have an audience
with me, what
would I say. I would tell him
Jesus loves

47:31.949 --> 47:40.691 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
him. I would tell him that there
is life beyond
June 17. And that's what I would
say.

47:40.725 --> 47:45.696 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I had the opportunity a couple
of weeks ago
to meet his aunt. She came to
me, and she

47:45.730 --> 47:52.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was a little timid, probably
wondering, what
would I say and how would I
react? And I saw

47:52.169 --> 47:58.476 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that she was crying. And I
reached out to
her to give her a hug, and she
stepped back,

47:58.509 --> 48:04.381 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and she said, "Well let me tell
you this first."
She said, "I'm Dylann Roof's
aunt."

48:04.415 --> 48:10.221 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I said, "But you still need a
hug. Can I hug
you?" And she said yes.

48:10.254 --> 48:12.256 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And then you
talked?

48:12.289 --> 48:14.091 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
REV. BETTY DEAS CLARK: And then
we talked,
and then we prayed. We did.

48:14.125 --> 48:19.563 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: I asked you at
the beginning
how your congregation is doing a
year later.

48:19.597 --> 48:29.673 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
What about the city, the
culture, all that
that provoked about race
relations in this

48:29.707 --> 48:31.575 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
country? Where do you see
things?

48:31.609 --> 48:35.713 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
REV. BETTY DEAS CLARK: Well,
while it may
have provoked the need to deal
with race relations,

48:35.746 --> 48:45.289 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it also brought to surface how
loving, how
caring and how united this city
really is,

48:45.322 --> 48:54.632 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
because, in the aftermath of
June 17, the
community joined together,
walked together,

48:54.665 --> 48:58.536 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
prayed together, worshiped
together.

48:58.569 --> 49:04.441 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so, while we do have a way
to go, we have
come a long way.

49:04.475 --> 49:05.309 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: You feel that?

49:05.342 --> 49:07.778 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
REV. BETTY DEAS CLARK: I
honestly do.

49:07.812 --> 49:16.053 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right, Rev.
Dr. Betty Clark,
thank you so much.

49:16.086 --> 49:26.897 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
REV. BETTY DEAS CLARK: Thank
you.

